Chief minister V Narayanasamy moved the resolution

PUDUCHERRY: The Puducherry legislative assembly on Wednesday unanimously passed a resolution urging the Centre to withdraw the Citizenship (Amendment) Act (CAA), the National Register of Citizens (NRC) and the National Population Register ( NPR ).Chief minister V Narayanasamy moved the resolution as soon as the assembly met at 9.30am. Congress and DMK members deliberated in detail on how the CAA, the NRC and the NPR would shatter the secular fabric of the country.The Opposition parties - All India NR Congress and AIADMK - boycotted the special session of the assembly. The three members nominated to the legislative assembly from BJP walked out of the assembly to register their protest against the governmentâ€™s decision to pass a resolution against the CAA, the NRC and the NPR.In the 30-member assembly, Congress has 14 seats (after Dhanavelu was removed from the party). Its ally DMK has three members, and a lone independent candidate from Mahe has extended support to Congress. On the opposition side, All India NR Congress has seven and AIADMK four members besides the three nominated BJP members.